This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category, as it deals with the problem of person re-identification using deep convolutional neural networks. The paper also proposes a novel method for training these networks, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of multiple training sets and the evaluation of performance could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories.
